'''阿列克谢·米亚切斯拉沃维奇·达尼洛夫'''（{{lang-uk|Олексій Мячеславович Данілов}}，{{bd|1962年|9月7日||}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itd.rada.gov.ua/mps/info/expage/8754/6|title=Данілов Олексій Мячеславович|work=[[Verkhovna_Rada|Verkhovna Rada]]|accessdate=October 3, 2019|lang=uk}}</ref>）[[乌克兰|乌克兰]]政治家<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kyivpost.com/ukraine-politics/zelensky-appoints-deputy-secretary-of-national-security-and-defense-council.html|title=Zelensky appoints deputy secretary of National Security and Defense Council|work=[[Kyiv_Post|Kyiv Post]]|author=[[Interfax-Ukraine|Interfax-Ukraine]]|date=July 23, 2019|accessdate=October 3, 2019}}</ref>，生于苏联乌克兰[[卢甘斯克州|卢甘斯克州]][[红卢奇|红卢奇]]，兽医专业毕业，2005年担任卢甘斯克州州长，[[2006年乌克兰议会选举|2006年乌克兰议会选举]]当选[[尤莉娅·季莫申科联盟|尤莉娅·季莫申科联盟]]议员，[[2007年乌克兰议会选举|2007年]]败选，自2019年10月起担任[[乌克兰国家安全与国防事务委员会|乌克兰国家安全与国防事务委员会]]秘书。<ref name="10707765-zelensky">{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/politics/10707765-zelensky-appoints-new-nsdc-secretary.html|title=Zelensky appoints new NSDC secretary|work=[[UNIAN|UNIAN]]|date=October 3, 2019|accessdate=October 3, 2019}}</ref>2022年2月25日起担任{{link-ru|乌克兰最高统帅部协调人|Ставка Верховного главнокомандующего (Украина)}}。

== 生平 ==
{{TransH}}
Danilov graduated in 1981 from the [[Starobilsk|Starobilsk]] State Farm Technical School with a degree in veterinary medicine.<ref name="danilova7252984"/> In 1981 he began working as a veterinary in a farm in [[Voroshilovgrad|Voroshilovgrad]] (currently Luhansk).<ref name="danilova7252984"/> From 1983 to 1987 he worked as a veterinarian in Voroshilovgrad's park "1 May".<ref name="danilova7252984"/> From 1987 to 1991 he worked as a private veterinarian.<ref name="danilova7252984"/> From 1991 to 1994 he was engaged in private entrepreneurship.<ref name="danilova7252984"/>

Danilov was Mayor of [[Luhansk|Luhansk]] from 1994 to 1997.<ref name="dnlv1"/> Aged 31 years, was the youngest mayor of Luhansk in the history of the city.<ref name="danilova7252984"/>

In the [[1998_Ukrainian_parliamentary_election|1998 Ukrainian parliamentary election]] Danilov unsuccessfully tried to win a parliamentary seat in electoral district 103 as an independent candidate.<ref name="chesno70168">{{cite web|url=https://www.chesno.org/politician/70168/|title=Electoral history of Oleksiy Myacheslavovych Danilov|work=[[Civil_movement_"Chesno"|Civil movement "Chesno"]]|accessdate=6 July 2020|lang=uk}}</ref>

In 1999, Danilov graduated from the [[University_of_Luhansk|University of Luhansk]] as a licensed history teacher.<ref name="danilova7252984"/> In 2000, Danilov received a [[master's_degree|master's degree]] in [[management|management]] from the [[East_Ukrainian_Volodymyr_Dahl_National_University|East Ukrainian Volodymyr Dahl National University]]. In 2000, he also received a [[law_degree|law degree]] from the [[Luhansk_State_University_of_Internal_Affairs|Luhansk State University of Internal Affairs]].<ref name="dnlv1">{{cite web|url=http://dovidka.com.ua/user/?code=41054|title=Данілов Олексій Мячеславович|work=dovidka.com.ua|accessdate=October 3, 2019}}</ref>

In the early [[2000s_(decade)|2000s]], Danilov was a member of the party Yabluko (that during his membership was renamed [[Party_of_Free_Democrats|Party of Free Democrats]]).<ref name="danilova7252984"/> In the [[2002_Ukrainian_parliamentary_election|2002 Ukrainian parliamentary election]] he was again unsuccessful in his attempt to get elected to parliament on the party list of this party.<ref name="chesno70168"/>

In 2000, Danilov was an adviser to the parliamentary Committee on Industrial Policy and Entrepreneurship.<ref name="danilova7252984"/> From October 2001 to February 2005, he founded the Luhansk Initiative and was its chairman. At the same time, he was as Deputy Director of the Institute for [[European_Integration|European Integration]] and Development.<ref name="dnlv2"/><ref name="danilova7252984"/>

Danilov served as the [[Governor_of_Luhansk_Oblast|Governor of Luhansk Oblast]] in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.president.gov.ua/documents/1782005-2143|title=Decree of the President of Ukraine № 178/2005|work=[[Office_of_the_President_of_Ukraine|Office of the President of Ukraine]]|accessdate=October 3, 2019|lang=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.president.gov.ua/documents/15612005-3340|title=Decree of the President of Ukraine № 1561/2005|work=[[Office_of_the_President_of_Ukraine|Office of the President of Ukraine]]|accessdate=October 3, 2019|lang=uk}}</ref>

Danilov was elected to the [[Verkhovna_Rada|Verkhovna Rada]] in [[2006_Ukrainian_parliamentary_election|2006]] for the [[Yulia_Tymoshenko_Bloc|Yulia Tymoshenko Bloc]].<ref name="dnlv2">{{cite web|url=https://112.international/ukraine-top-news/zelensky-appoints-danilov-as-secretary-of-national-defense-council-44178.html|title=Zelensky appoints Danilov as Secretary of National Defense Council|work=112 International|date=October 3, 2019|accessdate=October 3, 2019}}</ref><ref name="danilova7252984">{{cite web|url=https://www.unian.ua/m/politics/10707966-veterinar-i-vchitel-istoriji-shcho-vidomo-pro-novogo-sekretarya-rnbo-oleksiya-danilova.html|title=Veterinarian and history teacher: what is known about the new Secretary of the National Security and Defense Council Alexei Danilov|work=[[UNIAN|UNIAN]]|date=3 October 2019|accessdate=6 July 2020|lang=uk}}</ref> In the [[2007_Ukrainian_parliamentary_election|2007 Ukrainian parliamentary election]] Danilov tried to get reelected to parliament for the Party of Free Democrats, but was again unsuccessful in this.<ref name="chesno70168"/> After leaving parliament he returned the Institute of European Integration and Development to the previous position Deputy Director of the Institute for European Integration and Development.<ref name="danilova7252984"/>

Danilov was Deputy Secretary of the [[National_Security_and_Defense_Council_of_Ukraine|National Security and Defense Council]] from 23 July to 3 October 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.president.gov.ua/documents/5512019-28813|title=Decree of the President of Ukraine № 551/2019|work=[[Office_of_the_President_of_Ukraine|Office of the President of Ukraine]]|accessdate=October 3, 2019|lang=uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.president.gov.ua/documents/7322019-29865|title=Decree of the President of Ukraine № 732/2019|work=[[Office_of_the_President_of_Ukraine|Office of the President of Ukraine]]|accessdate=October 3, 2019|lang=uk}}</ref> Since 3 October 2019 he is the Secretary (deputy Chairman, President [[Volodymyr_Zelensky|Volodymyr Zelensky]] is the formal Chairman) of this Board.<ref name="10707765-zelensky"/><ref name="OleksiyDanilovukrainealert">[https://www.atlanticcouncil.org/blogs/ukrainealert/ukraines-unlikely-new-political-heavyweight/ Ukraine’s unlikely new political heavyweight] UkraineAlert by [[Adrian_Karatnycky|Adrian Karatnycky]], [[Atlantic_Council|Atlantic Council]] (31 March 2021)</ref> On 24 January 2022, Danilov said that the [[2021–2022_Russo-Ukrainian_crisis|movement of Russian troops]] near Ukraine's border was "not news" and "we don't see any grounds for statements about a full-scale offensive on our country."<ref>{{cite news |title=Ukraine urges calm, saying situation 'under control' and Russian invasion not imminent |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2022-01-26/ukraine-urges-calm-saying-russian-invasion-not-imminent/100781870 |work=ABC |date=25 January 2022}}</ref> 
